==English==
===Etymology===
From German [[Morgen]] "measure of land".
===Noun===
'''morgen'''
#  a unit of measurement of land in the Netherlands and the Dutch colonies, also used in [[Prussia]], [[Denmark]] and [[Norway]], equivalent to two [[acre]]s.

